Source: pgsql-http
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~), libcurl4-openssl-dev (>= 7)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/pramsey/pgsql-http

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-http
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-http
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: HTTP client for PostgreSQL PGVERSION
  HTTP client for PostgreSQL, retrieve a web page from inside the database.
  It can call a web service from SQL, either to get back a result or to poke
  that service into refreshing itself against the new database state.
